From 35b6047dd8586a7c730fefb40fdedc743e1431e5 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Wed, 17 Jun 2026 08:55:09 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Add sort/pagination to Manpower mapping, full dept list, ID
 doc verification modal
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

- OM Manpower manager mapping: sortable columns (click headers) and
  pagination at 10 rows per page with windowed page controls.
- Departments KPI card now lists all departments instead of "…more".
- Any identification value (PAN/CIN, GST, ESIC employer code, UAN, ESI)
  is now clickable, opening a modal with a mock document scan, parsed
  details, and Approve/Reject actions. Approving a contractor's
  documents raises its compliance score; rejecting lowers it, with the
  change propagated live to the vendor grid, drill-downs and directory.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>
Claude-Session: https://claude.ai/code/session_01XwhnhEioMKhFdcipFKn2xn
